- Always author documents via MyOsDsl.bootstrap() + DocumentBuilder; avoid raw Node trees unless unavoidable.
- Channels in contracts are abstract by default. Concrete identities belong in channelBindings (bindAccount / bindEmail).
- Use TypeAliases + PayNoteAliases + domain event builders (MyOsEvents / PayNoteEvents) for all event type construction.
- Prefer JsProgram + JsOutputBuilder + JsPatchBuilder + JsArrayBuilder/JsObjectBuilder for JavaScript step authoring.
- Every new example must include a matching test asserting:
  - document type/name
  - key channels/operations/workflows
  - at least one generated JS fragment for critical behavior
- If an operation allows broad mutation (for example directChange), attach policies with explicit changeset allow-lists.
- Keep minor units and human-readable amount text consistent in payment docs.
- Favor template -> specializer -> instance flow using DocTemplates.clone/extend/applyPatch for production-shaped PayNote issuance.
